00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 14=

19
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:41,120
Qing'e, I'll teach you how to
make small-portion stir-fries.

20
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:42,790
Do you know what that is?

21
00:01:44,110 --> 00:01:46,000
It's making just one dish per wok.

22
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,560
Everyone in the village does that.

23
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,400
Save it.

24
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:53,000
Can they make sautéed pork slices
or Guo Bao Rou?

25
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,320
Or chicken stew with mushrooms?

26
00:01:54,670 --> 00:01:56,350
They won't even know them.

27
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:59,760
Know why we use young
chickens for that stew?

28
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:01,440
Because the meat is tender.

29
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:02,280
Laidi,

30
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:03,480
go and

31
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:05,000
prepare a basket of potatoes.

32
00:02:07,670 --> 00:02:08,560
What's for breakfast?

33
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,750
Millet and mung bean porridge.

34
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:12,030
And for the solid part?

35
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:13,470
Cornmeal steamed cake.

36
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:16,030
How many beans are used?

37
00:02:16,390 --> 00:02:17,230
400 grams.

38
00:02:17,390 --> 00:02:18,920
250 grams is enough.

39
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,750
Just boil plain water, then.

40
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:23,280
You want it tasty, but add nothing?

41
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,750
How am I supposed to cook it?

42
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:25,590
Laidi.

43
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:28,150
Pass me the Mo basket.

44
00:02:28,150 --> 00:02:30,200
It's millet and mung bean porridge.

45
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,110
Not mung bean and millet porridge.

46
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:34,790
Millet is the lead. Mung beans are extras,

47
00:02:34,790 --> 00:02:35,750
only adding flavor.

48
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:37,960
You think mung beans are you?

49
00:02:38,390 --> 00:02:40,280
One says 250 grams, one says 400 grams.

50
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,350
Which one exactly?

51
00:02:41,350 --> 00:02:42,200
250 grams.

52
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,870
Fine. 250 grams it is.

53
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:44,720
You won.

54
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:46,200
Here, kid. Take it.

55
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,560
In case you get hungry.

56
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:50,590
400 grams.

57
00:02:51,950 --> 00:02:52,790
Master Song.

58
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:54,000
400 grams it is.

59
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,400
I want to sleep in the storeroom.

60
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,710
Why sleep in the storeroom?

61
00:02:58,790 --> 00:02:59,950
Is someone picking on you?

62
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:02,680
You can't sleep there.

63
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:03,840
It's damp and cold.

64
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,640
It's drafty, with mice too.

65
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,790
That's scary.

66
00:03:06,790 --> 00:03:07,640
I'm not scared.

67
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,000
Well, I am.

68
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,790
If anything happens to you,

69
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:12,280
how do I face your uncle?

70
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,590
Or the troupe?

71
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:17,040
What are you even thinking?

72
00:03:21,260 --> 00:03:22,940
(Award)

73
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:56,240
♪On the golden mountain in Beijing♪

74
00:03:56,240 --> 00:04:04,360
♪Chairman Mao is the golden sun♪

75
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:09,800
Yi Qing'e, what are you doing?

76
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,870
I'm asking you, dummy.

77
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,630
I'm not dumb.

78
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:24,000
Where's she going?

79
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,030
No idea.

80
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:26,240
Maybe going to the pigpen?

81
00:04:28,150 --> 00:04:29,000
For what?

82
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:30,630
So she can be back home.

83
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,150
I'll fix this hole later.

84
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:35,750
And I'll install a bolt.

85
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:37,590
Use this to block the door for now.

86
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,560
Tell me if you need me.

87
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,240
Get some sleep.

88
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,030
We have work tomorrow morning.

89
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,710
Keep the door blocked tight.

90
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:49,120
Uncle!

91
00:05:50,430 --> 00:05:51,910
Uncle!

92
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:57,510
Aunt Hua.

93
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,430
Master Song said you chose to sleep here.

94
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,360
I think it's a good idea.

95
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:15,000
It's better than being miserable with them.

96
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:22,000
I went to Beishan Prison today

97
00:06:22,310 --> 00:06:23,510
to see your uncle.

98
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,310
I brought him some things.

99
00:06:26,430 --> 00:06:27,510
How is he?

100
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,070
Like a different person.

101
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,630
Just like when you first arrived,

102
00:06:33,630 --> 00:06:34,630
he's gone silent.

103
00:06:36,310 --> 00:06:38,510
I told him all about you.

104
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:40,120
He tried to hide it,

105
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:42,040
but I could tell...

106
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:44,270
he cried.

107
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:53,120
He only said one thing to me.

108
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,160
He wanted you to keep practicing.

109
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:59,270
You promised him, didn't you?

110
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,720
Then you'd better keep your word.

111
00:07:12,870 --> 00:07:13,710
Come here.

112
00:07:18,870 --> 00:07:20,560
You're a kid from the mountains.

113
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,630
You haven't seen the world yet.

114
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:26,120
If city kids look down on you,

115
00:07:26,510 --> 00:07:27,680
that's not your fault.

116
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,430
You did nothing wrong.

117
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:34,680
I know you're hurt, but you're tough.

118
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,720
Opera takes endurance.

119
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:41,560
Endure the pain and the hurt inside.

120
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:45,390
But we can't just endure it.

121
00:07:46,430 --> 00:07:47,800
We have to learn to change.

122
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,920
You need real skill in you.

123
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:53,680
Whether others respect you or not

124
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,720
doesn't matter.

125
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:58,000
You must learn to respect yourself.

126
00:07:58,390 --> 00:07:59,230
You get it?

127
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,600
I'm scared.

128
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,440
Don't be.

129
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:16,240
Remember what I told you.

130
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,000
We all

131
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,870
have to rely on ourselves.

132
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:24,270
It's never easy.

133
00:08:27,190 --> 00:08:28,030
You can do it.

134
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,720
I have to leave tomorrow.

135
00:08:39,830 --> 00:08:40,720
Where?

136
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,200
To have my baby.

137
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:46,070
When will you be back?

138
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,720
I don't know.

139
00:08:50,390 --> 00:08:51,920
Look after yourself here.

140
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:56,740
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

141
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:57,590
Master Gou.

142
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,680
Can I ask you a favor?

143
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:01,350
What is it?

144
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:03,950
Sanyuan and I won't be around.

145
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:05,430
If the kid leaves this place,

146
00:09:05,430 --> 00:09:06,510
please check on her.

147
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:09,390
If anything comes up,

148
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,680
send word to me.

149
00:09:12,070 --> 00:09:12,910
No problem.

150
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:14,830
Hope all goes well for you.

151
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:17,120
Bring back a healthy baby soon.

152
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,870
Are we leaving or not?

153
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:20,390
I still need to train the kid later.

154
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:22,910
I'm off, then.

155
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,400
Be good.

156
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,270
Dachui, careful.

157
00:09:34,830 --> 00:09:36,000
Worry about yourself.

158
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:41,110
Keep practicing.

159
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,070
Hua Caixiang had left too,

160
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:50,360
making a new home in a far land.

161
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:54,120
She was Yi Qing'e's pillar of strength,

162
00:09:55,190 --> 00:09:58,120
yet she had lost her own support.

163
00:09:59,310 --> 00:10:02,070
Ever since joining the opera troupe,

164
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:06,160
Yi Qing'e had been saying goodbyes.

165
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,630
To Bayi.

166
00:10:09,270 --> 00:10:10,840
To Shoes Bai.

167
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,910
To Hu Sanyuan.

168
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:15,840
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

169
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,030
Watching her leave,

170
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:20,440
Yi Qing'e seemed to have grown stronger.

171
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:24,600
She had become used to partings.

172
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:40,620
♪A couple parted by life and death♪

173
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:49,580
♪The world's deepest pain♪

174
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:04,180
♪A month of sorrow♪

175
00:11:04,180 --> 00:11:07,340
♪Weighs heavy on my heart♪

176
00:11:07,340 --> 00:11:13,180
♪The moon is hazy tonight♪

177
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:16,740
♪Silence fills the fields♪

178
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:26,860
♪In the cold and desolate outskirts♪

179
00:11:27,620 --> 00:11:32,500
♪I cry for my wife♪

180
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:41,420
♪Since we were wed♪

181
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:47,200
It's all static. I can't hear clearly.

182
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:49,080
Is it really him singing?

183
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:53,200
It's Zhou Ren Hui Fu!

184
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:57,440
Even with static, I'd know Gu's voice

185
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,670
even a hundred years from now.

186
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:01,960
Have the old plays been liberated?

187
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:04,390
If they have been liberated,

188
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:06,870
then the three of us

189
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,200
will finally see the light of day.

190
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:20,390
Nice.

191
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:21,230
Nice!

192
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:22,960
Nice.

193
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,790
Nice. Nice!

194
00:12:26,790 --> 00:12:28,790
Stop tapping. Can't you see it's stuck?

195
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:31,270
Director Huang, you hit hard.

196
00:12:31,270 --> 00:12:32,600
Even Zhou Ren couldn't take you.

197
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,030
I heard it.

198
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:37,510
Zhou Ren Hui Fu, right?

199
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:40,120
Old plays can air again?

200
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,440
What are you trying to say?

201
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:45,910
I heard many out-of-town troupes

202
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:47,440
are restaging the old plays.

203
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:50,080
Shouldn't we provide
against a rainy day too?

204
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:53,240
Do you know where the rain's coming from?

205
00:12:54,390 --> 00:12:55,510
It's already on the radio.

206
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:57,150
Isn't that a signal?

207
00:12:57,510 --> 00:12:58,630
Who gave you that signal?

208
00:12:58,630 --> 00:12:59,550
Which radio station

209
00:13:00,150 --> 00:13:01,200
gave you that signal?

210
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:03,030
The Provincial People's Broadcasting Station.

211
00:13:04,870 --> 00:13:09,630
We should tune in to the Central
People's Broadcasting Station.

212
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:15,840
Be careful. Careful.

213
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,680
Next one.

214
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,720
You still have an appetite?

215
00:13:50,790 --> 00:13:51,630
What?

216
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:55,440
The radio just played the version of

217
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:58,360
Zhou Ren Hui Fu sung by Gu Cunxiao.

218
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,000
Old plays can be staged now?

219
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:02,840
I don't know.

220
00:14:03,870 --> 00:14:06,720
That aired on the Provincial
People's Broadcasting Station.

221
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:09,870
Listen to the Central
People's Broadcasting Station.

222
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,550
Isn't the provincial one run by the Party?

223
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:19,630
You're a gatekeeper.

224
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:20,960
Yet your mouth has no gate at all.

225
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,240
Stay calm.

226
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:27,200
Be patient.

227
00:14:29,390 --> 00:14:31,080
You can't rush hot tofu.

228
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:33,440
Where would we even get tofu?

229
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,200
Let me give you a warning.

230
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:38,790
The kids can't keep training like this.

231
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:42,240
With these showy moves for
the old plays, they're not even

232
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:43,670
fit for playing minor roles.

233
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:46,670
Planting rice when the pot's empty?

234
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:47,720
Too late.

235
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,560
True.

236
00:14:50,870 --> 00:14:53,320
Worry about rice in your own pot first.

237
00:14:57,910 --> 00:15:00,120
The ruler's calm, but the aide panics.

238
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:01,750
Shameless.

239
00:15:02,270 --> 00:15:03,110
Shameless.

240
00:15:04,540 --> 00:15:08,820
(Boiled water)

241
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,910
No, your waist is too loose.

242
00:15:19,910 --> 00:15:21,360
Soft as tofu. Look.

243
00:15:22,910 --> 00:15:25,630
Training isn't just arms. Use your waist.

244
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:29,240
Skip the waist, and you won't excel.

245
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:30,670
Come here.

246
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:32,480
Let me explain.

247
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:33,440
Tending the fire.

248
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,280
You can do both.

249
00:15:34,290 --> 00:15:35,240
Do another one. Come on.

250
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,080
Please move aside.

251
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,270
Why is this kid so stubborn?

252
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:40,920
Laidi.

253
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:42,790
Come in and give me a hand.

254
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:53,560
Go.

255
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:55,750
You still have room for improvement.

256
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:56,870
- Okay, next.
- Next.

257
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:57,990
Come on.

258
00:15:58,270 --> 00:16:00,120
What are you waiting for?

259
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:02,590
Straighten your arms.

260
00:16:03,510 --> 00:16:04,550
Okay. Go.

261
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:08,600
Are you dumb or what?

262
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:10,080
Why are you so slow?

263
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:12,790
Get up, get up.

264
00:16:12,790 --> 00:16:13,910
What did you say?

265
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:15,510
Did Director Huang scold you like that?

266
00:16:15,510 --> 00:16:17,080
I think the kid is doing great.

267
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,510
That's what Director Huang said.

268
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:20,630
He's slow, so he needs hard training.

269
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:22,120
He said that?

270
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,030
Are you dumb or what?

271
00:16:24,030 --> 00:16:25,150
Keep practicing!

272
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:26,630
One more try.

273
00:16:26,630 --> 00:16:27,550
Train harder.

274
00:16:27,550 --> 00:16:28,390
- Go.
- Go.

275
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:44,200
Why aren't you eating?

276
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,390
We eat last.

277
00:16:47,790 --> 00:16:49,480
What's the ration for kitchen workers?

278
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:51,840
No ration. Eat all you want.

279
00:16:52,510 --> 00:16:53,910
I want to join you.

280
00:16:54,270 --> 00:16:55,320
Can you think of a way?

281
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,480
Go ask your aunt.

282
00:16:58,480 --> 00:17:00,150
I did. Got beaten for it.

283
00:17:00,790 --> 00:17:01,670
Serves you right.

284
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:06,240
Since you left, I've become the worst one.

285
00:17:07,390 --> 00:17:08,230
So lonely.

286
00:17:08,910 --> 00:17:10,320
Train hard.

287
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,240
I do already.

288
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,550
They make it look easy.

289
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:16,030
I push the hardest and still lag behind.

290
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,480
No wonder they laugh at me.

291
00:17:18,910 --> 00:17:20,150
I even hate myself for it.

292
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:22,960
When will this ever end?

293
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:28,200
Do me a favor.

294
00:17:28,910 --> 00:17:29,750
What favor?

295
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:33,910
Train hard by day. Coach me at night.

296
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:35,120
We'll practice together.

297
00:17:36,870 --> 00:17:38,030
Aren't you tired?

298
00:17:39,260 --> 00:17:40,270
During that time,

299
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:44,560
one slow kid taught another the skills.

300
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:45,670
Three, two, one.

301
00:17:45,670 --> 00:17:48,270
Yi Qing'e didn't know why she practiced,

302
00:17:48,870 --> 00:17:51,340
- but she just wanted to.
- One more time.

303
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:55,120
Not only because she promised
Hu Sanyuan and Hua Caixiang

304
00:17:55,270 --> 00:17:57,410
she'd never give up.

305
00:17:57,410 --> 00:17:58,270
The hands.

306
00:17:58,270 --> 00:17:59,420
Why was she like this?

307
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:00,280
Then...

308
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:02,140
- She couldn't explain.
- Kick back hard.

309
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:03,080
Swing back hard.

310
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:04,480
Three, two, one, go.

311
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,160
Up, up, up.

312
00:18:08,030 --> 00:18:08,960
Why are you so dumb?

313
00:18:09,270 --> 00:18:10,600
I'm not dumb!

314
00:18:10,790 --> 00:18:12,670
Don't get angry.

315
00:18:12,670 --> 00:18:13,910
That's how the teacher scolds me.

316
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:16,440
It's not like a teacher without that word.

317
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:18,160
Try it again.

318
00:18:19,630 --> 00:18:21,270
One, two, three, go.

319
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,110
Listen.

320
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:26,720
Use both hands.

321
00:18:33,910 --> 00:18:36,600
Tighten up and use your core.

322
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,360
Why did you hit me?

323
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:39,600
For your own good.

324
00:18:40,270 --> 00:18:41,350
Leave me alone!

325
00:18:42,070 --> 00:18:43,480
Why are you so ungrateful?

326
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,160
You do it wrong. Let me teach you.

327
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,110
No need.

328
00:18:46,680 --> 00:18:48,030
Be a stoker forever?

329
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:49,700
What I do has nothing to do with you.

330
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:50,590
You're so stubborn.

331
00:18:50,590 --> 00:18:52,070
Even Hu Sanyuan doesn't talk back to me.

332
00:18:56,270 --> 00:18:57,750
Fine, then go back to your fire.

333
00:18:58,960 --> 00:18:59,880
You're finished.

334
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:02,000
No, you're finished.

335
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,160
Who is it?

336
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:12,000
Master Qiu.

337
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,000
Come with me.

338
00:19:30,550 --> 00:19:35,110
♪Your illness is fake♪

339
00:19:36,270 --> 00:19:40,480
♪I'm a fake doctor too♪

340
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:44,440
♪Patients can't tell I'm fake♪

341
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:55,070
Just go in.

342
00:19:56,310 --> 00:19:57,150
Go in.

343
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:15,390
Move.

344
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:46,000
Come on, lift your leg.

345
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:47,520
This one.

346
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:50,790
Straighten the other leg.

347
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:52,520
Higher.

348
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:56,840
Bend back.

349
00:20:57,720 --> 00:20:58,560
Bend back.

350
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,000
Lower.

351
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,790
Lock your legs. Lower.

352
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:06,440
This kid...

353
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,680
Tight tendons, stiff bones.

354
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,440
Not much hope.

355
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:11,550
If she wants to get good,

356
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,200
she'll have to suffer.

357
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:15,240
Really suffer.

358
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:17,750
No kid could endure that.

359
00:21:18,350 --> 00:21:19,400
This kid...

360
00:21:20,310 --> 00:21:21,720
has a spark in the eyes.

361
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:42,950
Kid.

362
00:22:44,310 --> 00:22:45,920
Do you know why I took you here?

363
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:51,480
Our troupe used to

364
00:22:51,750 --> 00:22:53,550
be called the Cunjia Troupe.

365
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:57,030
Master Gou was their leading star,

366
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:58,920
performing the Dan role.

367
00:22:59,790 --> 00:23:02,750
Master Zhou and I used to perform,

368
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:04,880
right here on this very stage.

369
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:06,830
Back then, Master Gou

370
00:23:06,830 --> 00:23:09,720
was a star performer for miles around.

371
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,550
The three of us will teach you.

372
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:15,550
Work by day, and take training by night.

373
00:23:15,830 --> 00:23:16,670
Kid,

374
00:23:17,110 --> 00:23:18,920
do you know why I chose you?

375
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:21,550
Because you're the best
in the trainee class.

376
00:23:22,270 --> 00:23:24,160
Those other teachers are blind.

377
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:26,270
None of them has my eye for talent.

378
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:28,750
You might look dumb, but you're not.

379
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:30,750
Out of everyone in the class,

380
00:23:30,750 --> 00:23:32,350
no one has a spark as bright as yours.

381
00:23:32,830 --> 00:23:34,440
It'd be a waste if you quit.

382
00:23:35,270 --> 00:23:36,160
I'll teach you.

383
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:39,310
Work hard and follow my instructions,

384
00:23:39,830 --> 00:23:41,550
and I'll make sure you make it.

385
00:23:42,350 --> 00:23:43,190
If I fail,

386
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:45,350
I'll die on the stage.

387
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:05,270
Yi Qing'e remembered her promise,

388
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:08,070
so she kept practicing in secret,

389
00:24:08,070 --> 00:24:09,830
never missing a single day.

390
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:12,590
Yet, she felt lost inside.

391
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:16,640
Cooking wasn't what she wanted to do,

392
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:18,350
but as for opera training...

393
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:20,640
even Ms. Hua and Ms. Mi

394
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:22,480
found it so difficult.

395
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,880
How could she ever succeed?

396
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:28,880
(Sealed by Ningzhou Police, May 15, 1977)
Gou Cunzhong came looking for her,

397
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:31,350
insisting she was a natural talent.

398
00:24:32,030 --> 00:24:34,000
He even risked her life.

399
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:36,880
Before this,

400
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:40,350
no one had ever valued her so much.

401
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:42,400
Tears welled in her eyes.

402
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:45,000
She wanted to cry, to scream.

403
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,240
But she knew

404
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:49,310
she was only a girl tending the fire.

405
00:24:50,110 --> 00:24:52,270
Helpless and torn.

406
00:24:52,590 --> 00:24:54,240
She thought it over and over.

407
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:57,960
But she still wanted to prove herself.

408
00:24:58,310 --> 00:25:00,200
You need real skill in you.

409
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:04,000
Whether others respect you
or not doesn't matter.

410
00:25:05,750 --> 00:25:08,000
You must learn to respect yourself.

411
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,160
You must keep learning the opera.

412
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,270
However hard it gets,

413
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:15,350
keep going.

414
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:17,070
We all

415
00:25:17,590 --> 00:25:18,750
have to rely on ourselves.

416
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:20,400
It's never easy.

417
00:25:23,270 --> 00:25:24,110
You can do it.

418
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:27,640
I need to hear you promise me.

419
00:25:29,510 --> 00:25:30,880
I promise you.

420
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:04,160
I'm in.

421
00:26:06,110 --> 00:26:07,480
To train with me,

422
00:26:08,030 --> 00:26:10,750
rather than with that trainee class,

423
00:26:11,310 --> 00:26:12,440
will be much harder.

424
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:14,750
I'm not scared.

425
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:18,310
If you start, you can't leave it unfinished.

426
00:26:19,750 --> 00:26:21,200
What does that mean?

427
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,720
It means quitting halfway.

428
00:26:25,270 --> 00:26:26,550
I won't quit halfway.

429
00:26:33,590 --> 00:26:35,110
This stays between the four of us.

430
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:36,830
Don't tell anyone else.

431
00:26:36,830 --> 00:26:37,670
Got it?

432
00:26:38,110 --> 00:26:38,950
Got it.

433
00:26:39,590 --> 00:26:42,880
At Master Zhou's, train each night.

434
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,790
Before you help them cook breakfast,

435
00:26:45,110 --> 00:26:46,400
practice one more hour on your own.

436
00:26:46,830 --> 00:26:47,880
Can you do that?

437
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:56,760
Laidi.

438
00:26:57,750 --> 00:26:59,510
It's late. Why are you still up?

439
00:27:00,110 --> 00:27:00,950
Waiting for you.

440
00:27:02,310 --> 00:27:03,150
Here.

441
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:06,640
Where did you get it?

442
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:08,240
Don't ask. Just eat.

443
00:27:15,110 --> 00:27:15,950
I swiped them.

444
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:18,960
It's fine.

445
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:20,880
Chu Jiahe secretly gave
them to Feng Xiaoxiao.

446
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:22,960
A lot. I only took two.

447
00:27:23,790 --> 00:27:25,200
He won't notice. Eat up.

448
00:27:28,310 --> 00:27:29,240
Where did you go?

449
00:27:30,070 --> 00:27:30,960
Don't ask.

450
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:32,910
Why not?

451
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:34,480
I can't tell you.

452
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:35,880
I don't keep secrets from you.

453
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:37,550
I even told you about the candy.

454
00:27:37,920 --> 00:27:39,440
I promised that person.

455
00:27:39,880 --> 00:27:40,720
Who?

456
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:45,550
Fine. Like I care anyway.

457
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,440
I got scolded again today.

458
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:54,480
When will these scoldings ever end?

459
00:27:59,310 --> 00:28:02,240
Actually, somersaults aren't just legs.

460
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:04,030
You need the waist strength.

461
00:28:04,030 --> 00:28:06,110
If your waist gives, you're done for.

462
00:28:08,510 --> 00:28:09,400
Who taught you that?

463
00:28:10,510 --> 00:28:12,830
Whoever teaches you, it takes hard work.

464
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,070
I'm slow.

465
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,240
No one can teach me.

466
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,680
I'm slow too.

467
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:24,030
It's not our fault we're slow.

468
00:28:24,030 --> 00:28:26,920
They'd be the same if born in the hills.

469
00:28:28,590 --> 00:28:30,590
Others might think we're dumb,

470
00:28:30,590 --> 00:28:32,510
but we can't think of ourselves as dummies,

471
00:28:32,510 --> 00:28:33,590
or we'd really be dummies.

472
00:28:34,110 --> 00:28:35,880
Why do you sound like a grown-up?

473
00:29:04,550 --> 00:29:06,790
Laidi, check out my new move!

474
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:07,880
I'll show you.

475
00:29:13,790 --> 00:29:15,070
Be careful.

476
00:29:18,270 --> 00:29:19,750
Laidi, what are you doing?

477
00:29:19,750 --> 00:29:20,790
Starting the fire.

478
00:29:22,310 --> 00:29:23,960
It's Sunday, so we only

479
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:25,110
eat twice.

480
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:26,510
I completely forgot.

481
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:27,750
What's wrong with you?

482
00:29:27,750 --> 00:29:29,510
Don't burn a hole in the pot.

483
00:29:29,510 --> 00:29:31,590
Let me flip another one!

484
00:29:33,310 --> 00:29:35,270
What's with Heiwa? So diligent.

485
00:29:40,350 --> 00:29:41,310
Heiwa.

486
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:45,200
Heiwa!

487
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:48,520
Heiwa!

488
00:29:52,790 --> 00:29:53,630
Heiwa!

489
00:29:53,750 --> 00:29:55,030
Heiwa! Heiwa!

490
00:29:55,270 --> 00:29:56,160
Heiwa!

491
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:57,000
What's the matter?

492
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,550
Heiwa, you okay?

493
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:00,390
Heiwa!

494
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:01,590
Heiwa.

495
00:30:01,590 --> 00:30:02,720
Don't touch him! Leave him be.

496
00:30:03,030 --> 00:30:03,960
Just watch him.

497
00:30:03,960 --> 00:30:05,160
Don't touch him. I'll get help.

498
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:06,320
Heiwa!

499
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:08,200
Laidi, don't touch him!

500
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:09,040
Heiwa.

501
00:30:09,750 --> 00:30:11,160
Heiwa. Heiwa.

502
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:13,150
Heiwa.

503
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:15,070
- What's wrong with you?
- Heiwa fell down!

504
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:19,720
That didn't count.

505
00:30:21,590 --> 00:30:22,590
Heiwa!

506
00:30:27,070 --> 00:30:28,160
Heiwa!

507
00:30:28,590 --> 00:30:29,680
Heiwa!

508
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:32,030
Heiwa, what's wrong?

509
00:31:33,270 --> 00:31:34,110
Eat.

510
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:36,960
As much as you want.

511
00:31:42,270 --> 00:31:44,270
You won't have to practice anymore.

512
00:31:50,030 --> 00:31:52,590
No more staying in the dorm alone.

513
00:31:55,590 --> 00:31:57,550
Since you left, I've become the worst one.

514
00:31:58,750 --> 00:31:59,830
So lonely.

515
00:32:00,510 --> 00:32:01,590
I got scolded again today.

516
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:04,830
When will these scoldings ever end?

517
00:32:08,510 --> 00:32:09,350
Here.

518
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,270
Eat.

519
00:32:25,790 --> 00:32:27,030
I'll eat with you.

520
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:56,200
I'm going to training.

521
00:34:39,260 --> 00:34:46,260
(Men)

522
00:34:48,180 --> 00:34:55,180
(Boiled water)

523
00:35:31,510 --> 00:35:33,310
The forward somersault was better.

524
00:35:33,310 --> 00:35:34,920
But don't practice alone yet.

525
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:36,550
During the day tomorrow,

526
00:35:36,550 --> 00:35:38,030
practice the other basics.

527
00:35:38,030 --> 00:35:38,990
Okay?

528
00:35:39,110 --> 00:35:40,270
Go back and get some rest.

529
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,510
Hey, go back and sleep.

530
00:36:37,550 --> 00:36:38,400
Turn it on.

531
00:36:38,710 --> 00:36:40,190
Mr. He...

532
00:36:40,190 --> 00:36:42,000
Chu Jiahe, save it.

533
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,110
Mr. He,

534
00:36:43,110 --> 00:36:45,280
it's Saturday. Let us have some fun.

535
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:46,360
You wish!

536
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:49,070
Dancing like demons.

537
00:36:50,110 --> 00:36:51,070
Look at yourselves.

538
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:52,710
During the training,

539
00:36:53,070 --> 00:36:55,150
your rear hurts, your head hurts,

540
00:36:55,150 --> 00:36:56,400
your toes hurt...

541
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:57,280
My fingernails hurt.

542
00:36:57,590 --> 00:36:58,440
Feng Xiaoxiao!

543
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:00,590
What? Not hurting now?

544
00:37:01,030 --> 00:37:02,630
No training, no pain.

545
00:37:02,940 --> 00:37:03,800
Cut the nonsense.

546
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:04,920
Can't hit me!

547
00:37:04,920 --> 00:37:06,360
Mr. He.

548
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:08,230
Saturday comes just once a week.

549
00:37:08,230 --> 00:37:10,710
Let us play a little longer.

550
00:37:10,710 --> 00:37:11,840
Chu Jiahe, Monday comes

551
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:13,230
just once a week too.

552
00:37:13,230 --> 00:37:14,480
Why don't you rise early?

553
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:16,960
Mr. He.

554
00:37:21,420 --> 00:37:22,280
Just one song.

555
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:23,120
Stop!

556
00:37:25,070 --> 00:37:25,910
Save it!

557
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:32,960
Spotlight, follow me.

558
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:35,160
Three songs!

559
00:37:50,300 --> 00:37:51,190
Feng Xiaoxiao,

560
00:37:51,190 --> 00:37:52,070
come here!

561
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,630
How embarrassing.

562
00:39:09,190 --> 00:39:10,920
The pants are

563
00:39:11,510 --> 00:39:13,000
on backward.

564
00:39:13,510 --> 00:39:15,480
But they swept the ground clean.

565
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:17,030
Those are called bell-bottoms.

566
00:39:17,670 --> 00:39:20,110
And what kind of dance is that?

567
00:39:20,110 --> 00:39:21,630
Having a fit?

568
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:24,320
It's in now. Young people love it.

569
00:39:25,070 --> 00:39:26,880
Can it stay in for thousands of years?

570
00:39:29,150 --> 00:39:31,320
Nothing outlasts the Qinqiang opera.

571
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:40,320
Feng Xiaoxiao.

572
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:41,710
Come help me.

573
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:45,670
Kids these days are really something.

574
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:48,030
They all think they're Nezha.

575
00:39:50,110 --> 00:39:51,480
What are you staring at?

576
00:39:51,480 --> 00:39:53,150
Push. I can't pedal anymore.

577
00:39:54,590 --> 00:39:56,590
One, two.

578
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,070
Easy now.

579
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:01,480
Hold tight.

580
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,670
Hold tight. Hold tight.

581
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:03,600
Speed it up.

582
00:40:10,920 --> 00:40:13,440
(The Qinqiang opera San Di Xue)
♪A plan♪

583
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:16,510
♪Send word to Shaanxi, check it through♪

584
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:22,110
This half pig I bought is really fatty.

585
00:40:22,110 --> 00:40:25,190
The fat alone is two fingers thick.

586
00:40:25,190 --> 00:40:26,710
That was three.

587
00:40:27,630 --> 00:40:29,110
Come on, unload it.

588
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:32,360
Unload it.

589
00:40:38,630 --> 00:40:39,880
Why the long face?

590
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:41,840
Someone's trying to take over.

591
00:40:42,230 --> 00:40:43,070
Who?

592
00:40:45,670 --> 00:40:46,510
Take over what?

593
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:50,190
The knife and ladle. He wants Head Chef.

594
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:53,480
That jerk.

595
00:40:54,590 --> 00:40:56,070
Making stuff up again.

596
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:00,230
Master Liao?

597
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:02,230
Having tea?

598
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:07,960
Why are you so angry?

599
00:41:07,960 --> 00:41:09,190
Can he even cook?

600
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:12,280
The twice-cooked pork was
burnt the last time.

601
00:41:12,550 --> 00:41:13,760
He can't even stir-fry

602
00:41:14,590 --> 00:41:15,550
shredded potatoes well.

603
00:41:15,710 --> 00:41:18,550
The bun filling was way too salty.

604
00:41:18,550 --> 00:41:19,960
The stuff he makes

605
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:22,070
is burnt, salty, and sticky.

606
00:41:22,070 --> 00:41:22,920
Kid. Kid.

607
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:24,190
Stop moving things.

608
00:41:24,510 --> 00:41:25,350
Take a break.

609
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:27,880
Go. Take a break.

610
00:41:28,510 --> 00:41:30,960
A pig feeder as the head chef?

611
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:32,710
Embarrassing!

612
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:37,110
Everyone makes mistakes sometimes.

613
00:41:38,230 --> 00:41:40,070
It was just a one-off for Master Song.

614
00:41:40,070 --> 00:41:41,630
You can't just dismiss him.

615
00:41:41,630 --> 00:41:42,480
What...

616
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:44,360
You can't just write him off,

617
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:45,200
right?

618
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:47,710
No, let's talk about me instead.

619
00:41:48,150 --> 00:41:49,760
You shouldn't waste my talent, right?

620
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,920
- Go on.
- Using a sword to kill a flea?

621
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:55,400
When Director Huang transferred you,

622
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:58,000
didn't we agree you'd be the sous chef?

623
00:41:58,000 --> 00:42:00,710
We have to be practical, right?

624
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:03,710
I was a chef at Chang'an Restaurant.

625
00:42:03,710 --> 00:42:06,510
Being a sous chef for a pig feeder?

626
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:08,230
Does that seem right?

627
00:42:11,510 --> 00:42:12,710
So what do you suggest?

628
00:42:13,110 --> 00:42:14,280
I'm a reasonable man.

629
00:42:14,550 --> 00:42:16,190
Here's my plan.

630
00:42:16,190 --> 00:42:17,320
The position of

631
00:42:17,590 --> 00:42:19,590
Head Chef should rotate every week.

632
00:42:21,110 --> 00:42:22,030
Can you decide that?

633
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:25,400
Or should Director Huang talk to you?

634
00:42:26,030 --> 00:42:28,070
Don't bother him with this.

635
00:42:28,070 --> 00:42:29,360
It's no big deal.

636
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:30,280
Drink tea.

637
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:32,190
I'll talk it over with Master Song.

638
00:42:32,510 --> 00:42:33,510
Just drink.

639
00:42:34,800 --> 00:42:36,000
No big deal.

640
00:42:42,440 --> 00:42:43,280
Master Qiu.

641
00:42:43,510 --> 00:42:44,350
Drawing water?

642
00:42:50,400 --> 00:42:51,590
A bully with backing.

643
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:56,920
Using his ties to Huang Zhengjing.

644
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,920
He's just being unreasonable.

645
00:43:02,550 --> 00:43:03,800
Don't stoop to his level.

646
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

647
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:10,770
You must stand tall.

648
00:43:11,250 --> 00:43:12,800
Acting is about portraying life.

649
00:43:12,950 --> 00:43:15,100
Your reach goes from
the gate to the kitchen!

650
00:43:15,100 --> 00:43:15,940
Pooh!

651
00:43:15,940 --> 00:43:17,160
I'll teach you a lesson.

652
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:20,310
Zhou Ren Hui Fu!

653
00:43:20,310 --> 00:43:23,110
The lead Wusheng of the Cun generation.

654
00:43:23,470 --> 00:43:24,750
Please, Master Gu.

655
00:43:25,380 --> 00:43:26,390
A 17-year-old,

656
00:43:26,390 --> 00:43:28,470
learning from a 60-year-old,

657
00:43:28,470 --> 00:43:31,620
became so old-fashioned.

658
00:43:31,920 --> 00:43:33,270
What do you mean by that?

659
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

660
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

661
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

662
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

663
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

664
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

665
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

666
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

667
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

668
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

669
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

670
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

671
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

672
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

673
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

674
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

675
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

676
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

677
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

678
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

679
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

